First, identify the starting and ending shareholders' equity from the balance sheet:

- Initial Equity (2023-12-31): 13,000,000.00
- End Equity (2024-01-29): 11,824,937.81

Next, calculate the net income (net profit) over the period:

- Net Profit (2024-01-29): -1,175,062.19

Since ROE is calculated as:

\[
ROE = \frac{\text{Net Income}}{\text{Average Shareholders' Equity}} \times 100\%
\]

Calculate the average equity:

\[
\text{Average Equity} = \frac{13,000,000 + 11,824,937.81}{2} = 12,412,468.91
\]

Compute ROE:

\[
ROE = \frac{-1,175,062.19}{12,412,468.91} \times 100\% \approx -9.47\%
\]

Rounding to two decimal places, ROE is approximately -9.47%.

---
